I"a<p>This example shows how to add more files (such as <code class="language-plaintext highlighter-rouge">*.h</code> and <code class="language-plaintext highlighter-rouge">*.cpp</code>) to a current Arduino project without making it into an <a href="https://www.arduino.cc/en/Hacking/libraryTutorial">Arduino library</a>.</p>

<p>Example folder structure:</p>

<div class="language-plaintext highlighter-rouge"><div class="highlight"><pre class="highlight"><code>.
├── Makefile
├── main.ino
└── src
    └── foo
        ├── foo.cpp
        └── foo.h
</code></pre></div></div>
